list-item.p:
Mice were vaccinated three times with AAV vectors or two times with WIV and then challenged with a lethal dose of homologous influenza virus (Cal/7/9) (A, B; 
      n = 5) or two different lethal doses of the heterologous PR8 strain (C, D; 
      n = 6 and E, F; 
      n = 7). Survival was monitored over a 14‐day period and is depicted as Kaplan–Meier plot (A, C, E). Weight loss was determined during the 14‐day period, which is shown in relation to the weight at day 0 (B, D, F). Mean ± SE. Statistical significance between negative control group (AAV‐GFP) or WIV group (E), and each vaccine group was determined using log‐rank (Mantel–Cox) test (*
      P < 0.05, **
      P < 0.01).
